  <entry>
    <id>https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/beef-and-yellow-split-pea-stew-with-crispy-potatoes</id>
    <title>Beef and yellow split pea stew with crispy potatoes</title>
    <updated>2026-04-18T17:19:04.101242+00:00</updated>
    <content type="html">&lt;h1 style="text-align:center;font-family:sans-serif;"&gt;Beef and yellow split pea stew with crispy potatoes&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;img src="https://www.strangerfoods.org/images/beef-and-yellow-split-pea-stew-with-crispy-potatoes.webp" style="text-align:center;"/&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;p style="font-family:sans-serif;&gt;To me, this dish represents an Iranian take on the classic meat and potato comfort dish, with a few unique ingredients, of course! Persian dried limes, or limu omāni, provide a bold, tangy citrus taste with deep, earthy, fermented undertones.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/beef-and-yellow-split-pea-stew-with-crispy-potatoes"/>
    <published>2026-04-04T00:00:00+00:00</published>
