  <entry>
    <id>https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/tuna-kokoro-bowl</id>
    <title>Tuna kokoro bowl</title>
    <updated>2026-04-18T17:19:04.100703+00:00</updated>
    <content type="html">&lt;h1 style="text-align:center;font-family:sans-serif;"&gt;Tuna kokoro bowl&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;img src="https://www.strangerfoods.org/images/tuna-kokoro-bowl.webp" style="text-align:center;"/&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;p style="font-family:sans-serif;&gt;In Japanese, kokoro has no direct translation but, in essence, it means ‘heart, mind and body’ so it is the perfect name for a nutrient-rich bowl to feed the body and soul. It is our take on the traditional Hawaiian poké bowl, which serves fresh raw fish with fresh raw vegetables. Prepared simply, taste and texture lead the way.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/tuna-kokoro-bowl"/>
    <published>2026-04-11T00:00:00+00:00</published>
